From: Shengjing Zhu <zhsj@debian.org>
Date: Sun, 28 Jul 2024 19:44:27 -0400
Subject: Use system-installed googletest via CMake package discovery

Rebased for opencc 1.4.0: the ENABLE_GTEST block gained a bundled-source
existence check ahead of the USE_SYSTEM_GTEST branch since this patch
was written, so the else() is now attached further down; only that
if/else/endif is touched here.

Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-07-04
---
--- OpenCC.orig/CMakeLists.txt
+++ OpenCC/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -309,6 +309,8 @@ endif()
 if (ENABLE_GTEST)
   if(NOT USE_SYSTEM_GTEST)
     add_subdirectory(deps/googletest-1.15.0)
+  else()
+    find_package(GTest CONFIG REQUIRED)
   endif()
   enable_testing()
 endif()
